<task id="MCI-019" project="M365 Copilot Integration R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>AdaptiveCardFormatterService</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, adaptive-cards, service</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>MCI-010, MCI-016, MCI-017, MCI-018</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the AdaptiveCardFormatterService — a .NET service that transforms BFF API responses
    (playbook output JSON, entity data, search results) into Adaptive Card JSON payloads.
    The service loads card templates created in MCI-016/017/018, populates them with dynamic
    data, and returns ready-to-send card JSON for the Agent Gateway to include in Copilot
    responses.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer experienced with JSON templating, Adaptive Cards SDK, and BFF API patterns</role>

  <goal>
    Deliver a registered, tested AdaptiveCardFormatterService that can transform any supported
    BFF API response type into the correct Adaptive Card JSON payload using the template
    library from Phase 3 card tasks.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    - Follow ADR-010: DI minimalism — register as a single service, not per-card-type
    - Load card templates from embedded resources or a known file path at startup
    - Use AdaptiveCards.Templating NuGet package for data-binding
    - Handle all card types: document-list, document-card, matter-summary, task-list, playbook-menu, risk-findings, playbook-library, progress-indicator, email-preview, handoff-card, wizard-launch, error-card
    - Return serialized JSON string ready for Copilot response attachment
    - Throw descriptive exceptions for unknown card types or template binding failures
    - Keep the service stateless (templates loaded once, no per-request state)
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/service-registration.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Review the card templates from MCI-016, MCI-017, MCI-018 to understand data-binding placeholders</step>
    <step order="2">Create AdaptiveCardModels.cs with request/response models for each card type — typed input models that map BFF API responses to card data shapes</step>
    <step order="3">Create AdaptiveCardFormatterService.cs with constructor that loads all card templates and a FormatCard method that accepts card type enum and data object</step>
    <step order="4">Implement template loading — read JSON templates from embedded resources or cards/ directory at startup</step>
    <step order="5">Implement data binding using AdaptiveCards.Templating — expand templates with provided data models</step>
    <step order="6">Implement error card formatting as a fallback for any rendering failures</step>
    <step order="7">Register service in DI following ADR-010 patterns (single AddSingleton registration)</step>
    <step order="8">Add unit tests for each card type transformation with sample input data</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Glob</tool>
    <tool>Grep</tool>
    <tool>Bash</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Features/Agent/AdaptiveCardFormatterService.cs</output>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Features/Agent/Models/AdaptiveCardModels.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - AdaptiveCardFormatterService is registered as singleton in DI
    - FormatCard method accepts a card type and data object, returns valid Adaptive Card JSON string
    - All 12 card types (from MCI-016/017/018) are supported
    - Templates are loaded once at startup and cached in memory
    - Invalid card type throws ArgumentException with descriptive message
    - Template binding failure returns error card JSON instead of throwing
    - AdaptiveCardModels.cs contains typed models for each card data shape
    - Unit tests cover at least one sample transformation per card type
    - Service follows ADR-010 (single DI registration, no per-type interfaces)
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
